{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-tsx","path":"/2019/03/24/blender-tutorial-10-light-part-1/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p><em>In this new post of the series Blender tutorial I will talk about light.</em></p>\n<hr>\n<p>In the <a href=\"/2019/03/23/blender-tutorial-9-textures-part-2/\">previous post of the series \"Blender tutorial\"</a> we talked\nabout textures in Blender. In this post we will explore lights in Blender.<br>\nFirst of all we need to clarify one thing: lights in Blender are called lamps. So in all menus and option we will find\nthat word to identify lights.<br>\nTo add a light to our scenes, just use the option Add -> Lamp and select one of the light type available. Let's add for\nexample a simple point light.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/dc02901539cdd2de4221e64a26f34139/c58a3/blender-add-light.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.50877192982456%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Add a light to the scene\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/dc02901539cdd2de4221e64a26f34139/0470c/blender-add-light.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/dc02901539cdd2de4221e64a26f34139/6c669/blender-add-light.jpg 285w,\n/static/dc02901539cdd2de4221e64a26f34139/882a4/blender-add-light.jpg 570w,\n/static/dc02901539cdd2de4221e64a26f34139/0470c/blender-add-light.jpg 1140w,\n/static/dc02901539cdd2de4221e64a26f34139/c58a3/blender-add-light.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Add a light to the scene</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>We can then customize the light properties using the related tab in the properties panel. In this section you can find\nspecific customizable properties for each type of light. For example for a point light we can customize:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>the falloff of the light, so how the light decrease when you get away from it</li>\n<li>negative, to transform the light so that it will subtract illumination from the scene</li>\n<li>diffuse and specular, so that the light will be used to render only specular or diffuse component of a material</li>\n<li>energy, how much bright the light is</li>\n<li>distance, the maximum light distance at which it will still affect objects</li>\n</ul>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/b88c00f73473fadea89ef0d7f4b86ee2/c58a3/blender-point-light.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.50877192982456%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Point light properties panel\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/b88c00f73473fadea89ef0d7f4b86ee2/0470c/blender-point-light.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/b88c00f73473fadea89ef0d7f4b86ee2/6c669/blender-point-light.jpg 285w,\n/static/b88c00f73473fadea89ef0d7f4b86ee2/882a4/blender-point-light.jpg 570w,\n/static/b88c00f73473fadea89ef0d7f4b86ee2/0470c/blender-point-light.jpg 1140w,\n/static/b88c00f73473fadea89ef0d7f4b86ee2/c58a3/blender-point-light.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Point light properties panel</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>For the point light (and also some other kind of light) it is possible to enable shadows. To do that we have to choose\nray shadow in the light properties panel and customize the look and feel of the shadow. Here we can also define the\nnumber of samples to be used to generate the shadows: the higher the better shadow we obtain (if you want to know more\nabout ray tracing shadows, you can\nread <a href=\"https://www.cim.mcgill.ca/~langer/557/19-slides.pdf\" title=\"ray tracing shadow rays\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">this lecture</a>. To actually render\nthe shadow, we need also to set the shadow flag enable in the renderer settings properties panel.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/09c17b4a72ee4ce62841e30ca7b83cbf/c58a3/blender-shadow-enable-1.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.50877192982456%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Shadow panel properties\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/09c17b4a72ee4ce62841e30ca7b83cbf/0470c/blender-shadow-enable-1.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/09c17b4a72ee4ce62841e30ca7b83cbf/6c669/blender-shadow-enable-1.jpg 285w,\n/static/09c17b4a72ee4ce62841e30ca7b83cbf/882a4/blender-shadow-enable-1.jpg 570w,\n/static/09c17b4a72ee4ce62841e30ca7b83cbf/0470c/blender-shadow-enable-1.jpg 1140w,\n/static/09c17b4a72ee4ce62841e30ca7b83cbf/c58a3/blender-shadow-enable-1.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Shadow panel properties</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/97a3e2c213ec2a26998093d6b5b0d64c/c58a3/blender-shadow-enable-2.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.15789473684211%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Enable shadow in the shading section\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/97a3e2c213ec2a26998093d6b5b0d64c/0470c/blender-shadow-enable-2.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/97a3e2c213ec2a26998093d6b5b0d64c/6c669/blender-shadow-enable-2.jpg 285w,\n/static/97a3e2c213ec2a26998093d6b5b0d64c/882a4/blender-shadow-enable-2.jpg 570w,\n/static/97a3e2c213ec2a26998093d6b5b0d64c/0470c/blender-shadow-enable-2.jpg 1140w,\n/static/97a3e2c213ec2a26998093d6b5b0d64c/c58a3/blender-shadow-enable-2.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Enable shadow in the shading section</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>There are other types of lights. For example we have spot lamps. These are light with a specific dim that simulate a\ncone of light. We can customize its properties in the light tab in the properties panel. One thing to note for spot\nlight is that we can customize the cone (shape, size...).</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/72165577be6c7a581bb61295d91aa75c/c58a3/blender-spot-light.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 58.94736842105264%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"A spot light\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/72165577be6c7a581bb61295d91aa75c/0470c/blender-spot-light.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/72165577be6c7a581bb61295d91aa75c/6c669/blender-spot-light.jpg 285w,\n/static/72165577be6c7a581bb61295d91aa75c/882a4/blender-spot-light.jpg 570w,\n/static/72165577be6c7a581bb61295d91aa75c/0470c/blender-spot-light.jpg 1140w,\n/static/72165577be6c7a581bb61295d91aa75c/c58a3/blender-spot-light.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">A spot light</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>Spot light can use a new type of shadow called buffer shadow. They are useful because they can be rendered more quickly.\nAfter enabling it in the properties panel of the spot light, we can customize it as always. There are different type of\nbuffer shadow:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Classical</li>\n<li>Classical Half</li>\n<li>Irregular, a method to achieve ray-tracing alike shadows with good performance</li>\n<li>Deep, another method similar to ray tracing but much more expensive in terms of performance then Irregular</li>\n</ul>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/022fec322f1827956168e5ab5605b417/c58a3/blender-spot-light-shadow.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 58.94736842105264%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Add shadow to a spot light\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/022fec322f1827956168e5ab5605b417/0470c/blender-spot-light-shadow.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/022fec322f1827956168e5ab5605b417/6c669/blender-spot-light-shadow.jpg 285w,\n/static/022fec322f1827956168e5ab5605b417/882a4/blender-spot-light-shadow.jpg 570w,\n/static/022fec322f1827956168e5ab5605b417/0470c/blender-spot-light-shadow.jpg 1140w,\n/static/022fec322f1827956168e5ab5605b417/c58a3/blender-spot-light-shadow.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Add shadow to a spot light</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>Another type of light is Hemi-lamps. This are used to create an overall directional light for you scene. As a\nconsequence of the fact that it is a directional light, the position of it doesn't change the final lighting result.\nOnly the orientation influences the final lighting result. As always, we can customize its behaviour in the properties\npanel.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/2aabe6c006fbe5d594358a6239b4cf1a/c58a3/blender-hemi-lamps.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 58.94736842105264%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"A hemi lamps\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/2aabe6c006fbe5d594358a6239b4cf1a/0470c/blender-hemi-lamps.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/2aabe6c006fbe5d594358a6239b4cf1a/6c669/blender-hemi-lamps.jpg 285w,\n/static/2aabe6c006fbe5d594358a6239b4cf1a/882a4/blender-hemi-lamps.jpg 570w,\n/static/2aabe6c006fbe5d594358a6239b4cf1a/0470c/blender-hemi-lamps.jpg 1140w,\n/static/2aabe6c006fbe5d594358a6239b4cf1a/c58a3/blender-hemi-lamps.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">A hemi lamps</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>The last available type of light is the area lamps. This kind of light provide illumination from a specific region\nrather than a single point or a single direction. We can customize it as always from the properties panel. One important\nthing to note is that area light as a distance property instead of falloff. This parameter determines the final\nattenuation result. the distance is represented in the 3D window as a dashed line. The only type of shadow supported the\nray traced shadow. We can also customize the shape of the shadow: different shapes influence the final rendering result.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/79be9cb8570a30ba6826dc7477b1316e/c58a3/blender-area-lamps.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 59.298245614035096%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"An area lamps\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/79be9cb8570a30ba6826dc7477b1316e/0470c/blender-area-lamps.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/79be9cb8570a30ba6826dc7477b1316e/6c669/blender-area-lamps.jpg 285w,\n/static/79be9cb8570a30ba6826dc7477b1316e/882a4/blender-area-lamps.jpg 570w,\n/static/79be9cb8570a30ba6826dc7477b1316e/0470c/blender-area-lamps.jpg 1140w,\n/static/79be9cb8570a30ba6826dc7477b1316e/c58a3/blender-area-lamps.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">An area lamps</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>In the next post we will talk about how to do other cool stuff with lights in Blender.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Blender tutorial: light - part 1","comments":true,"authors":["fabrizio_duroni"],"tags":["computer graphics","blender"],"date":"24 Mar 2019","description":"In this new post of the series Blender tutorial I will talk about light.","math":false,"image":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"fullWidth","backgroundColor":"#f8f8f8","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/72165577be6c7a581bb61295d91aa75c/943d5/blender-spot-light.jpg","srcSet":"/static/72165577be6c7a581bb61295d91aa75c/de80e/blender-spot-light.jpg 750w,\n/static/72165577be6c7a581bb61295d91aa75c/ce114/blender-spot-light.jpg 1080w,\n/static/72165577be6c7a581bb61295d91aa75c/ae726/blender-spot-light.jpg 1366w,\n/static/72165577be6c7a581bb61295d91aa75c/943d5/blender-spot-light.jpg 1500w","sizes":"100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/72165577be6c7a581bb61295d91aa75c/1d2c8/blender-spot-light.webp 750w,\n/static/72165577be6c7a581bb61295d91aa75c/917c4/blender-spot-light.webp 1080w,\n/static/72165577be6c7a581bb61295d91aa75c/9d9eb/blender-spot-light.webp 1366w,\n/static/72165577be6c7a581bb61295d91aa75c/d1888/blender-spot-light.webp 1500w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"100vw"}]},"width":1,"height":0.5900000000000001}}}},"fields":{"slug":"/2019/03/24/blender-tutorial-10-light-part-1/","readingTime":{"text":"4 min read"}}},"site":{"siteMetadata":{"author":"Fabrizio Duroni"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/2019/03/24/blender-tutorial-10-light-part-1/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2055070849","3076394108","379746230","4028829600"],"slicesMap":{}}